[h1]Very good VISUAL NOVEL with decent PIXEL GRAPHICS. But don't take it as a [i]bartender simulator.[/i][/h1]

[b]I must admit something. First, I came to VA-11 Hall-A because of the female protagonist. Second, I believe I have confused this game's description: I was expecting more action than gossip.[/b]

[b]+[/b] The new Nendoroid Jill Stingray and Fore; I have no funds right now, but I need Jill in my desk. Someday somehow;

[b]+[/b] Cyberpunk dystopia gossips about delicate subjects in real world;

[b]+[/b] Soundtrack. Love it;

[b]+[/b] Terms that I never heard or read before in games'dialogs, like "solipsistic crisis" or "semantic satiation". A prolific storyteller here, I guess.


[b]-[/b] There aren't dialogue options. To me, personally, it's a negative aspect;

[b]-[/b] Searching for recipes is not practical, it could be better;

[b]-[/b] Can't change control options. I was super bored pressing spacebar when I read someone else's guide in which pressing [spoiler]R-CTRL[/spoiler] skips an entire conversation. This kind of thing must be clear at the beginning, specially if you're going through a second run.

I guess you can sit back and relax, eating and drinking for while IF you're curious enough about the characters' past (and actual) lives; otherwise it's a long, tedious "press to skip" game.
Don't get me wrong: these people have a sick mind when it comes to writing a novel.
First, I went to get the achievements. Some mistakes along the way. Discovered that must play a second, maybe a third time to get them all.
There's no second, I gave up.


I give it a 8.0/10.
Do not overestimate the game, like: "unlike anything else", "stunning adventure".
No. Please. It's closer to [url=https://www.destructoid.com/reviews/review-va-11-hall-a/]Destructoid[/url], a fine and original video game.
